comment:
* Class used by apps to request the content capture service to remove data associated with * {@link LocusId LocusIds}. * *

An app which has tagged data with a LocusId can therefore delete them later. This is intended * to let apps propagate deletions of user data into the operating system.

variables.name: FLAG_IS_PREFIX
variables.comment:
* When set, service should use the {@link LocusId#getId()} as prefix for the data to be
     * removed.

methods.name: public String getPackageName()
methods.comment: * Gets the name of the app that's making the request.

methods.name: public boolean isForEverything()
methods.comment: * Checks if app is requesting to remove content capture data associated with its package.

methods.name: public List<LocusIdRequest> getLocusIdRequests()
methods.comment: * Gets the list of {@code LousId}s the apps is requesting to remove.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel parcel, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel parcel, int flags)
